# Frontend Accessibility Guard

Apply this rule when changing UI components, styles, or interaction behavior.

## Required Checks

- Text-size modes remain functional (`Small`, `Medium`, `Large`, `XL`).
- High-contrast mode remains legible across touched views.
- Mobile menu/modal behavior keeps overlay + outside-click + Escape handling consistent.
- Touch target sizing remains usable on mobile.

## Style Consistency

- Prefer Tailwind utilities for component styling.
- Use global CSS only for shared primitives/tokens.
- Keep style updates aligned with docs in `docs/styleguide/`.

## Pre-Commit

- Ensure UI behavior/documentation are updated together when UX changes.
